Recursion is a basic programming technique you can use in Java, in which a method calls itself to solve some problem.    A method that uses this technique   is recursive. Many programming problems   can be solved only by recursion, and some problems that can be solved by other techniques are better solved by recursion.  EXP-1: Factorial 	 	public static long factorial(int n){         if (n == 1)             return 1;         else             return n * factorial(n-1);     }  EXP-2: Fibonacci 	 	static int n1=1, n2=2, n3=0;     public static void printFibo(int count){         if (count > 0) {             n3 = n1 + n2;             n1 = n2;             n2 = n3;             System.out.print(" " + n3);             printFibo(count-1);         }     }
